Armed Hand Fight: The MP3 Player vs. Mobile.
We advise you how to choose
While almost all mobile plays MP3 files, no MP3 player gets to make calls.
Which seems clear that it is better to buy only the phone.
There are still enough reasons for man to acquire only the breeder.
The choice depends practically on the manner of its use and the requirement of the future owner.
It will probably be difficult for him to acquire the most modern record player to listen to Maxim Turbulenc’s latest album on it.
On the other hand, this type of musical products such as LP records no longer come out, and as far as their quality is concerned, there is not a single objective reason to continue buying them.
If vinyl records with art rock, jazz or blues music are crowded on your shelves, you are probably dreaming, at least, of this type of record player.
This is the same with the music that is on the way, that is, the compressed, simplified music - the music in MP3.
And here there are categories of price and quality.
For some it may be unacceptable to spend eight thousand crowns on a player, as well as for a Pink Floyd lover who will hardly taste the twenty crown market helmets.
Two extremes, between which there is enough space for each.
The choice is wide.
It also decides the battery life
Some of the best players get much more than just playing music and even what not even most mobile phones.
No current device is as universal as the phone.
Faced with the most elementary functions such as calling, sending messages, it can play music and video, record both, has a better or worse camera and can even get to navigate.
And when we take into account the Smartphone and the PDAs they will also have in their pocket a small computer.
This is a small miracle since no refrigerator can make a grill and no television can photograph.
The universality of mobiles also brings us disadvantages.
The more features you use on your mobile phone, the earlier the display indicator will light up asking to be recharged.
And music playback is one of the biggest energy dragons.
Few mobile phones manage to play music for more than ten or twelve hours, most much less.
In this sense, music players (especially the simplest ones) clearly perform better.
Therefore, keep in mind that cheap mobile phones will not play more than two hours.
If in addition to this, on top of it, they constantly call themselves still, for more safety, a charger for the job - this also applies to the most expensive appliances.
With the MP3 player this problem is not going to have, because even the worst endure at least 9 hours of uninterrupted operation after a charge.
Another problem occurs when recording music on mobile.
Unfortunately only a part of the devices has the universal USB connector and, moreover, not all of them can be connected directly to the computer without special software.
Of course it is possible to record music directly on the memory card but only in some unreduced drives can connect the small memory cards that are used in mobile phones.
On players, with some exception (iPod), no special software is required.
Simply fill the device with music via the computer’s USB.
