The Prague MHD takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, in the history of the Prague Transport Company is written the date when the first passengers enter the metro, tram and bus with an electronic voucher in their pockets instead of a paper ticket.
This can be purchased at the moment by almost one hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
