The two candidates in the U.S. presidential elections, who have been late in the negotiations, were rather in favour of the agreement, without forgetting to express their dissatisfaction with being forced to reach this extremity.
Democratic Senator Barack Obama was given certain provisions to reach the agreement, particularly one that would allow homeowners to retain their domicile and the salary of the leaders of surviving state-owned businesses.
" When taxpayers are asked to take extraordinary action because of the irresponsibility of some, there is no need to congratulate themselves.
