Students victims of expensive rent, up to 900 euros for a room
The rent market for college students does not know the crisis.
According to the latest survey of Sunia, the tenant union, renting a single room could cost a student 900 euros in Milan, 700 in Florence, 650 in Naples, 600 in Rome.
"the phenomenon has already assumed very serious characteristics to the point of excluding the right to study a large part of young people because of the very high costs that the family would have to sustain - explains the head of the Sunia studies office, Laura Mariani - in these cities the strong demand has totally deformed the market to such an extent that it triggers a process of widespread increase even for the residents".
Apart from the fact that in most cases the rental offers contain a number of violations: free type contracts, unregistered, no-canon limit, sub-linked rentals.
